Yes. The app registers **`GET /health`** in Express:

```40:42:backend/src/app.ts
  app.get("/health", (_req, res) => {
    res.json({ ok: true });
  });
```

Railway is pointed at that same path in config:

```6:10:backend/railway.json
  "deploy": {
    "startCommand": "node dist/index.js",
    "preDeployCommand": [
      "npx prisma migrate deploy --schema src/prisma/schema.prisma"
    ],
    "healthcheckPath": "/health"
  }
```

So the path exists in code and matches what Railway healthchecks use.

